The University of Nairobi through the kavi institute for clinical research together with a consortium of African universities and research institutions has initiated the sisulu foundation for African and pandemic disease response. The foundation, led by Walter Sisulu university from south Africa is set to establish a collaborative pan African platform for training, research and development in pandemics. Speaking during the launch, acting director general of health Dr. Patrick Amoth said the foundation will enable Africans to develop their own covid 19 vaccines as well as combat other diseases and pandemics in future.